{
  "stem": "3360.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we had gotten a letter from the husband of my father's sister, who gave the affidavit, that we were to bring nothing but our clothes, really, with us because there was no room to store it.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That turned out to be a big lie because the man had a big business here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "When-- that if he couldn't store it in his beautiful, gorgeous apartment on [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Belmont ?] Avenue, then he could have stored it somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So we, we had-- we came with, really, nothing, with, you know, clothes on our backs and what was in the suitcases.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they allowed us, then, to take two place settings of silver per person.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That was the German government's allowance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And so that's-- you know, the time was passed doing that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "In the meantime, we had had-- my father, you know, dared to be-- dared not to be seen very much outside anymore.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We had always enjoyed a wonderful afternoon at the Elbe River, out in a suburb that was called-- it's called Blankenese, B-L-A-N-K-E-N-E-S-E, where you sit way up on a cliff-like area.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And you look down to the river.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And you see the ships-- the passenger ships pulling out to the North Sea.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was on the way to the North Sea.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The river was very wide there already.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "You'd hear the band playing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And, you know, people were going to have a wonderful passage going over there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And there was-- there were, you know, cakes and-- excuse me-- petit fours to be bought.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And my parents would drink coffee.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And it was very nice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You could sit there all afternoon and enjoy the sights.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we no longer went there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
